<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="85" type="conservation status">
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
<pageBreakToken pageId="4" pageNumber="85" start="start">Conservation</pageBreakToken>
status.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="4" pageNumber="85">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koc &amp; Hamzaoglu" authorityYear="2015" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Bolanthus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bolanthus turcicus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="4" pageNumber="85" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="turcicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="85">Bolanthus turcicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an endemic species known only from the type gathered in the Hasan Mountain (Aksaray province). Informal grazing and land-use changes could have a detrimental impact in the future. For this reason this species should be classified as &quot;Critically Endangered&quot; (CR-B1a) according to the World Conservation Union categories (
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="Notes Royal Botanic Garden" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" publicationUrl="http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B10" refString="IUCN, 2014. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 11, February 2014., http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf [accessed 25 December 2014]" title="Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 11, February 2014" url="http://jr.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2014">IUCN 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
